 Dictionary SPA — README

 Project Overview

This is a Single Page Application (SPA) built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript that allows users to search for any English word and retrieve its definitions, pronunciation, synonyms, and source details — all without reloading the page.

It was built as part of a web development lab focused on API integration, DOM manipulation, and modern JavaScript practices.



 Features

-Word Search — Type any English word and fetch its data from a live dictionary API
- Definitions — View multiple definitions grouped by part of speech (noun, verb, adjective, etc.)
- Pronunciation — See the phonetic spelling of the word
- Audio Playback — Click the speaker button to hear the word pronounced out loud
- Synonyms — Browse synonym tags; click any tag to instantly search that word
- Source Links — Direct links to the original dictionary source
- Error Handling — Friendly messages for empty input or words not found
- Responsive Design — Works on desktop and mobile screens


 Technologies Used

| Technology | Purpose |

| HTML5 | Page structure and semantic markup |
| CSS3 | Styling, animations, hover effects, responsive layout |
| JavaScript (ES6+) | API calls, DOM manipulation, event listeners |
| Free Dictionary API | Word data (definitions, phonetics, synonyms) |
| Google Fonts | Typography (Playfair Display, DM Sans) |



 API Used

Free Dictionary API
- URL: `https://api.dictionaryapi.dev/api/v2/entries/en/{word}`
- Free to use, no API key required
- Returns: definitions, part of speech, phonetics, audio, synonyms, and source URLs



## How to Run the App

1. Download the file `dictionary.html`
2. Open it in any modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, or Edge recommended)
3. Make sure you have an **internet connection** (required for the API and Google Fonts)
4. Type a word in the search bar and click **Search**

> No installations, no server, no setup required. Just open and use!

