## File Structure

Since this is a single-file SPA, everything is contained in one file:

```
dictionary.html
├── HTML  — Page structure (header, form, results section)
├── CSS   — All styles (embedded in <style> tag)
└── JS    — All logic (embedded in <script> tag)
```

---

## JavaScript Functions Explained

| Function | Description |
|---|---|
| `fetchWord(word)` | Sends a fetch request to the Dictionary API |
| `getPhonetics(data)` | Extracts phonetic text and audio URL from API response |
| `getSynonyms(data)` | Collects all unique synonyms from the API response |
| `renderResults(data)` | Builds and inserts all result cards into the DOM |
| `doSearch(word)` | Main function: validates input, calls fetch, handles errors |
| `showLoader()` | Displays the spinning loading indicator |
| `hideLoader()` | Hides the loading indicator |
| `showError(msg)` | Displays an error message to the user |
| `clearResults()` | Clears previous search results from the page |
| `safe(str)` | Escapes HTML characters to prevent XSS security issues |

---

## Error Handling

| Scenario | What Happens |
|---|---|
| Empty search input | Shows warning: "Please type a word before searching" |
| Word not found in API | Shows error: "Was not found. Check spelling and try again" |
| No synonyms available | Synonyms section is hidden automatically |
| No audio available | Audio button is hidden automatically |
| No example sentence | Example line is hidden automatically |

